Here are all the steps to send EC2 logs to CloudWatch:

Step 1 — IAM Role banao EC2 ke liye

IAM → Roles → Create Role
EC2 select karein
Yeh policy attach karein: CloudWatchAgentServerPolicy
Role naam dein: EC2-CloudWatch-Role
Create Role


Step 2 — Role EC2 se attach karo

EC2 → Apna instance select karein
Actions → Security → Modify IAM Role
EC2-CloudWatch-Role select karein → Update


Step 3 — CloudWatch Agent install karo
EC2 mein SSH karke yeh commands chalao:
bash# CloudWatch Agent download karo
sudo dnf install amazon-cloudwatch-agent -y

Step 4 — Agent configure karo
bash# Configuration wizard chalao
sudo /opt/aws/amazon-cloudwatch-agent/bin/amazon-cloudwatch-agent-config-wizard
Wizard mein yeh options select karein:
On which OS are you running? → 1 (Linux)
Are you running on EC2? → 1 (Yes)
Root or non-root? → 2 (non-root)
Do you want to turn on StatsD? → 2 (No)
Do you want to monitor CPU? → 2 (No)
Do you want to monitor logs? → 1 (Yes)
Log file path → /var/log/messages
Log group name → my-ec2-logs
Log stream name → {instance_id}

Step 5 — Ya manually config file banao
bashsudo nano /opt/aws/amazon-cloudwatch-agent/etc/amazon-cloudwatch-agent.json
Yeh paste karein:
json{
  "logs": {
    "logs_collected": {
      "files": {
        "collect_list": [
          {
            "file_path": "/var/log/messages",
            "log_group_name": "my-ec2-logs",
            "log_stream_name": "{instance_id}",
            "timestamp_format": "%b %d %H:%M:%S"
          },
          {
            "file_path": "/var/log/secure",
            "log_group_name": "my-ec2-secure-logs",
            "log_stream_name": "{instance_id}",
            "timestamp_format": "%b %d %H:%M:%S"
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  }
}

Step 6 — Agent start karo
bash# Agent start karo
sudo /opt/aws/amazon-cloudwatch-agent/bin/amazon-cloudwatch-agent-ctl \
    -a fetch-config \
    -m ec2 \
    -c file:/opt/aws/amazon-cloudwatch-agent/etc/amazon-cloudwatch-agent.json \
    -s

# Status check karo
sudo systemctl status amazon-cloudwatch-agent

# Enable karo taaki reboot pe bhi chale
sudo systemctl enable amazon-cloudwatch-agent

Step 7 — CloudWatch mein logs dekho

AWS Console → CloudWatch
Left menu → Logs → Log Groups
my-ec2-logs dhundein
Andar jaao → Log Streams → Apna instance ID select karein
Logs dikhengi! ✅

